OL,3,CMSP makes Mother's Day call urging UK
OL,4,CGovernment to extend maternity pay
OL,6,FShe said that too many people are
OL,7,Fbeing forced to decide against having
OL,8,Fchildren for financial reasons and
OL,9,Fthat those who want a family "should
OL,10,Fnot be deterred by poor parental pay".
OL,12,FThe MSP suggested that expanding
OL,13,Fsupport for statutory maternity,
OL,14,Fpaternity and shared parental leave
OL,15,Fcould be paid for through wealth taxes.
OL,17,FShe said: "The early days of a child's
OL,18,Flife are vital, and every new parent
OL,19,Fshould have the opportunity to spend
OL,20,Fquality time with them and to
OL,21,Fintroduce them to the world.
OL,26,@qD@^OUrD@eO]yD@KOU
